{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Log in!{% endblock %}
{% block body_class 'login-img' %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="page">
        <div class="page-single">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col mx-auto">
                        <div class="text-center mb-6">
                            <img src="/assets/images/brand/logo.png" style="max-width:200px">
                        </div>
                        <div class="row justify-content-center">
                            <div class="col-md-8">
                                <div class="card-group mb-0">
                                    <div class="card p-4">
                                        <div class="card-body">
                                            <h1>Register</h1>
                                            {{ form_start(form) }}
                                                {{ form_widget(form) }}
                                                <div class="row">
                                                    <div class="col-12">
                                                        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block px-4">create a new account</button>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            {{ form_end(form) }}
                                            <p style="margin-top:30px">Already have an account?</p>
                                            <a href="{{ url('login') }}" class="btn btn-secondary active">Sign in</a>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="card text-white bg-primary py-5 d-md-down-none login-transparent">
                                        <div class="card-body text-center">
                                            <div>
                                                <p>The Bible was written to be shared and discussed in community. Early Christians gathered together to hear God’s Word and discuss the ways to live it out in everyday life.</p>
                                                <p>Nowadays many of us can read the Bible but it’s often a solitary experience. We don’t get to talk about what encourages us or challenges us about a passage. Gather is an online space for you to discuss scripture with friends throughout the week.</p>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
